title: Hanselman Unplugged at SSW
eventShortDescription: ​Scott Hanselman is in Australia as a special guest presenter at NDC Sydney and will be stopping in at SSW to give a talk at an extra-special Sydney user group, where he will be presenting 2 x 1-hour sessions
eventDescription:
​Scott Hanselman is in Australia as a special guest presenter at NDC Sydney and will be stopping in at SSW to give a talk at an extra-special Sydney user group, where he will be presenting 2 x 1-hour sessions:

Session #1: What you need to know

Come and find out from Scott Hanselman what you need to know to be a great developer in 2016.

Session #2: Hanselman Unplugged – open Q&A

This is your chance to ask Scott any questions on life at Microsoft, the future direction of .NET and any other technical or pop culture geek questions you may have.​

For those of you who can't make it in person, this event will also be live-streamed at https://www.ssw.com.au/ssw/Live/ 

IMPORTANT : although this is a free event, you need to register to get a ticket from
https://www.eventbrite.com/e/hanselman-unplugged-at-ssw-tickets-26676296521 ​
to secure your ticket! :)

Afterwards, join us for a beer at the Oaks across the road​
